findings.suggestion:
Refactor CronJobRecord into a discriminated union on `mode`:

interface BaseJob { id: string; name: string; handler: string; ... }
interface AtJob extends BaseJob { readonly mode: 'at'; readonly schedule: string /* ISO date */ }
interface EveryJob extends BaseJob { readonly mode: 'every'; readonly intervalSeconds: number }
interface CronExprJob extends BaseJob { readonly mode: 'cron'; readonly expression: string }
export type CronJobRecord = AtJob | EveryJob | CronExprJob

This also avoids the String(intervalSeconds) / Number(record.schedule) conversions in cron-service.ts.

