findings.suggestion:
Add a runtime guard before the cast:

function isScheduleMode(s: string): s is ScheduleMode {
  return s === 'at' || s === 'every' || s === 'cron'
}

In mapRow: if (!isScheduleMode(row.mode)) throw new Error(`Invalid mode in DB: ${row.mode}`)

Or use a Valibot schema for the full row: const CronJobRecordSchema = v.object({ mode: v.picklist(['at', 'every', 'cron']), ... })

